/>      char buf[1024];<br />      lseek(fd, 0, SEEK_SET);<br />      read(fd, buf, sizeof(buf));<br />   }<br /><br />or similar. But it's important that they all share the same struct file.<br /><br />It's also likely to make it easier to trigger the race if you have a<br />kernel with preemption enabled.<br /><br />And you need to have SLAB debugging enabled to actually *see* the<br />messages. Otherwise you'll have just (possibly silent) corruption or a<br />memory leak.<br /><br />              Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
